'''Colette Appel''' (born July 22, 1986 in [[Hartford, Connecticut]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]]. With former partner [[Lee Harris (figure skater)|Lee Harris]], she is the 2002 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships|U.S. junior champion]]. They placed 12th at the [[2002 World Junior Figure Skating Championships]]. Before teaming up with Harris, Appel competed with [[Adam Kaplan]] on the intermediate and novice levels. They were the 1998 U.S. pairs champions on the intermediate level and the 1999 U.S. novice silver medalists.
